data.title: InventHelp inventor from Thomasville, GA creates multi-language call controller solution for patients (MHO-492) - Oct. 31, 2025.
data.description: In Pittsburgh on October 31, 2025, a registered nurse from Thomasville, Georgia shared her invention aimed at helping patients of diverse language backgrounds to navigate medical call systems. The inventor expressed her motivation to streamline communication by simplifying the understanding of buttons and functions on the call system controller. This innovation addresses the obstacle faced by non-English speaking patients, enhancing their access to medical assistance. The invention could potentially benefit a considerable number of individuals requiring medical attention in healthcare facilities.

data.title: EU and US compete for influence with Turkey through defense deals. €9 billion Eurofighter Typhoon jets deal signed. EU and US leaders push for closer ties with Ankara amid NATO rivalry. Erdogan describes deal with UK as strengthening alliance. Germany supports Turkey's participation in European defense initiative. US-Turkey business deals for aircraft, nuclear power plant, LNG supplies. Trump and Erdogan share similar global order views. US-Turkey relations look to counter EU influence. EU-designed €150-billion program aims to enhance military capabilities.
data.description: The EU and US are strengthening ties with Turkey to increase influence in NATO, with Britain signing a €9 billion deal for 20 Eurofighter Typhoon jets. The agreement between British PM Starmer and President Erdogan is aimed at boosting security, defense cooperation, and economic growth. German Chancellor Merz also visited Turkey, expressing support for the country's participation in a €150 billion European defense initiative. The visits follow a meeting between US President Trump and Erdogan, where the leaders discussed business deals on aircraft, a nuclear power plant, and LNG supplies. The Brookings Institution noted similarities between Trump and Erdogan's global outlook. The EU and US seek to counter US influence with Turkey through these engagements.

data.title: Dominion Energy surpasses expectations with $1.06 in non-GAAP earnings per share, up from 98 cents last year, on $4.527 billion total revenue, marking a 14.99% increase from last year. Announced $112 million CVOW project cost charge. Resilient performance noted.
data.description: Dominion Energy, Inc. posted a strong performance in Q3 of 2025, surpassing expectations with an operating earnings (non-GAAP) of $1.06 per share, higher than the estimated 95 cents and up from 98 cents in Q3 2024. Total operating revenue also exceeded projections, reaching $4.527 billion, a 14.99% increase from the prior year's $3.941 billion. GAAP net income for the quarter stood at $1.16 per share. The stock of Dominion Energy, Inc. (NYSE: D) is showing upward momentum, indicating positive market sentiment towards the company. For more details, refer to the latest news updates.

data.title: Charter's Q3 revenue decreased to $13.67B, missing estimates; stock drops as internet, video losses grow, with 109,000 internet customers lost.
data.description: Charter Communications Inc (NASDAQ: CHTR) shares fell following its disappointing fiscal third-quarter 2025 results. The company saw a 0.9% decrease in quarterly revenue, reaching $13.67 billion, falling short of the expected $13.74 billion. Earnings per share came in at $8.34, missing the consensus estimate of $9.37. Revenue decline was due to lower residential video and advertising sales. Charter lost 109,000 internet customers in comparison to a decline of 110,000 in the same period last year. This loss included disconnects related to the end of the FCC's Affordable Connectivity Program in the third quarter of 2024. Additionally, the company saw a decline of 70,000 residential video customers.

data.title: CGTN article focuses on Xi Jinping championing openness and multilateralism at APEC with vision for Asia-Pacific community.
data.description: At the recent 32nd APEC Economic Leaders' Meeting held in Gyeongju, an article by CGTN emphasized the significance of Chinese President Xi Jinping's leadership in promoting openness and multilateralism in the region. The article highlighted President Xi's strategic vision for fostering an Asia-Pacific community. It discussed the various initiatives put forth during the event and underscored the importance of cooperation among member nations. President Xi's proactive approach and emphasis on multilateralism were seen as crucial for advancing regional economic integration. The article showcased how his engagement during the meeting provided guidance on key issues, with a focus on enhancing collaboration and fostering sustainable development. This highlights the growing importance of China's role in shaping the economic landscape of the Asia-Pacific region.

data.title: Hyundai Motor Group partners with NVIDIA to develop AI industry in Korea through new AI application and technology centers.
data.description: Hyundai Motor Group and NVIDIA have partnered with the South Korean government to advance South Korea's physical artificial intelligence industry. This collaboration will include creating an AI application center and AI technology center. The aim is to foster local AI talent and cultivate a thriving innovation ecosystem within Hyundai Motor Group.
